headline: From software to real estate, U.S. sectors under the grip of AI scare trade
summary: Wall Street is in the grip of disruption worries from AI. It first started with investors dumping shares of software companies but soon spread to sectors seen as vulnerable to automation, driving sharp losses in U.S. stocks this week. The AI scare trade did not spare even sectors ‌such as private credit, real estate brokers, data analytics, legal services and insurers.

headline: Three Stocks Priced Below Estimated Value In February 2026
summary: As February 2026 begins, the U.S. stock market is experiencing a strong start, with major indices like the Dow Jones Industrial Average and S&P 500 showing significant gains. In this environment of optimism and economic developments such as trade deals and shifts in monetary policy, identifying stocks that are priced below their estimated value can offer potential opportunities for investors looking to capitalize on market movements.
